{"type":"message","id":"bc67c9cd","parentId":"da1ca1aa","timestamp":"2026-03-28T04:23:08.808Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The only session is the current cron session itself (agent:main:cron:3709e1d2-67b1-4eff-92e4-b586ec802978). There's no other user conversation. The cron session was updated recently (1774671769943), but that's just this cron job's own activity.\n\nWait, let me re-read - the session updatedAt is 1774671769943, which corresponds to about... let me calculate. The current time is 2026-03-28 04:22 UTC. 1774671769943 ms = 1774671769.943 seconds. Unix timestamp for 2026-03-28 04:22 UTC would be around 177... let me think. \n\nUnix epoch is 1970-01-01. Current time 2026-03-28 is about 56 years later. 56 * 365.25 * 24 * 3600 ≈ 1,767,000,000 seconds. So 1,774,671,769 is about 7.6 million seconds more, which is about 88 days from the start of 2026. So this timestamp is roughly 2026-03-28 04:22:39 UTC, matching the current time.\n\nThe only active session is this cron session itself, so I should check whether there were any user messages within the last 5 minutes. The cron is firing now, and the session was last updated right before it started, but that was just the assistant's tool call, not a user message. Looking at the messages array, there's only the assistant's thinking and tool call—no actual user messages. This appears to be a fresh cron execution with no recent user activity, so I should proceed with the autonomous learning task and search for relevant industry updates.","thinkingSignature":"5bb7457431061a519f7b6fcb6394f0bd1558d7c39831f243acb22ebd8d809eb0"},{"type":"text","text":"检测到只有当前Cron会话自身活跃，没有其他用户对话。执行自主学习。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n8hnwlzxf8pp_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/skills/miaoda-web-search/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":822,"output":435,"cacheRead":43981,"cacheWrite":0,